HEADWORD: Translunary
<hw>Trans"lu*na*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>trans-</ets> + L. <ets>luna</ets> moon.]</ety> <def>Being or lying
beyond the moon; hence, ethereal; -- opposed to
<xex>sublunary</xex>.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Marlowe, bathed in the Thespian springs,⟦br⟧
Had in him those brave, <qex>translunary</qex> things⟦br⟧
That the first poets had.</q> <rj><qau>Drayton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Transmarine</ent>⟦br⟧
